    question: "Electron microscopy of a skeletal muscle fiber at rest shows thick (myosin) filaments 1.6 micrometers in length and thin (actin) filaments 1.0 micrometers long. During maximal shortening, what happens to the lengths of the A-band, I-band, and H-zone, according to the sliding filament model?",
