    question: "A dermatology resident is performing a punch biopsy of a pigmented lesion. The biopsy shows melanocytes in the basal layer of the epidermis. Each melanocyte has dendritic processes contacting multiple surrounding keratinocytes. What is the ratio of melanocytes to keratinocytes in the epidermis, and how do melanocytes transfer melanin to keratinocytes?",
